### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

common

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Recently I noticed that httpResource perform or not perform request  when the linked signal changes. The behaviour is based on how we define the httpResource.

## Happy case

If the httpResource defined the following way:

```ts
  protected POSTS_PER_PAGE = 10;
  protected skip = signal(0);

  postsResponse = httpResource<PostsResponse>(
    () => `https://dummyjson.com/posts/?skip=${this.skip()}&limit=${this.POSTS_PER_PAGE}`,
  );
```

Then whenever we change the value of the `skip` signal the _dummyjson.com_ gets called.

## Unhappy case

If the httpResource defined the following way:

```ts
  protected POSTS_PER_PAGE = 10;
  protected skip = signal(0);

  postsResponse = httpResource<PostsResponse>(
    {
      url: `https://dummyjson.com/posts/`,
      params: {
        skip: this.skip(),
        limit: this.POSTS_PER_PAGE,
      },
    },
  );
```
Then whenever we change the value of the `skip` signal the _dummyjson.com_ is not getting called.

If we change the code a bit, the behaviour won't change:
```ts
  protected POSTS_PER_PAGE = 10;
  protected skip = signal(0);

  postsResponse = httpResource<PostsResponse>(
    {
      url: `https://dummyjson.com/posts/?skip=${this.skip()}&limit=${this.POSTS_PER_PAGE}`,
    },
  );
```

